reviews.text: Good station. Nice warm waiting room. Coffee shop on the platform. Big clean toilets.

Arrived at the station in plenty of time and sat in the waiting area, listening for the train to be announced. I noticed other people wandering round looking for our train - apparently it had gone! Some of us went over to the enquiries office and they swore blind that the train had been announced "several times". Funny how all of us random strangers missed it...Two staff came over to check the tannoy, after a quick visit to the platform office - hey presto - it works, loud too! No explanation except we all must have missed the announcements. Very poor indeed, no wonder franchises are going bust.

Good service, train on time but..... 
The cleaning lady that look after the station ignore a passanger lady that try to ask her a question, as she is on her phone (headphone) and let me tell you, the language she use is so out of order. 
She must to argue over the phone and swear right a front of us passengers.

So big NO for that !!
Had a small  ticket problem. Dawn fixed it - fantastic service thank you.
